episodes.title: Bart's Not Dead
episodes.plot: Bart ends up in the hospital after taking a dare and lies about going to heaven to cover it up, but Homer takes a deal with Christian producers to make a movie about it.

episodes.title: Heartbreak Hotel
episodes.plot: Marge and Homer travel to a tropical island and go on Marge's favorite reality competition program to win a million dollars.

episodes.title: My Way or the Highway to Heaven
episodes.plot: While God and St. Peter discuss who will get into heaven, the citizens of Springfield recall divine encounters.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror XXIX
episodes.plot: Homer wins an oyster-eating contest against the mythical Cthulhu, Springfield is overrun by plant body-snatchers, Lisa finally snaps and Mr. Burns opens a retirement home with some Jurassic upgrades.

episodes.title: Baby You Can't Drive My Car
episodes.plot: A self-driving car company comes to Springfield, poaching all of the power plant employees with their fun work environment.

episodes.title: From Russia Without Love
episodes.plot: Bart, Nelson and Milhouse get a mail-order bride for Moe as a hardcore prank.

episodes.title: Werking Mom
episodes.plot: In search of a job, Marge gets one selling plastic food storage containers - as a drag queen; Lisa tries to make the world better.

episodes.title: Krusty the Clown
episodes.plot: Krusty hides out at a circus after he nearly kills Homer, who becomes a TV recapper and gives him a bad grade.

episodes.title: Daddicus Finch
episodes.plot: Bart feels neglected when Homer and Lisa bond over To Kill a Mockingbird and start spending quality time together, so Marge attempts to help Homer balance attention between the kids.

episodes.title: 'Tis the 30th Season
episodes.plot: Marge is determined to fix Christmas following a failed Black Friday shopping spree, but Homer and the kids surprise her with a vacation in Florida.

episodes.title: Mad About the Toy
episodes.plot: Motivated by a PTSD episode Grampa had while babysitting the kids, the Simpsons take a journey to Grampa's past as a post-WW2 toy model for plastic army men, and Abe finally faces his on confused sexuality.

episodes.title: The Girl on the Bus
episodes.plot: Lisa tries to live a double life when she makes a new friend and gets a taste of what it would be like to live with a more cultured family.

episodes.title: I'm Dancing as Fat as I Can
episodes.plot: Homer tries to make amends for binging his and Marge's favorite show without her; Bart prepares for "Krusty's Holiday Trample".

episodes.title: The Clown Stays in the Picture
episodes.plot: On Marc Maron's podcast, Krusty reveals the untold story of his past movie project, The Sands of Space. Hearing the podcast, Bart and Lisa learn their parents were production assistants on the movie in the early days of their relationship.

episodes.title: 101 Mitigations
episodes.plot: Homer steals Comic Book Guy's car and must either prove his innocence in court or reconcile with him.

episodes.title: I Want You (She's So Heavy)
episodes.plot: When a romantic night ends in injury for Homer and Marge, Lisa turns to an unlikely source to fix their strained relationship.

episodes.title: E My Sports
episodes.plot: Homer discovers a passion for coaching Bart in video game competitions; Lisa's plan to bring Homer back to reality creates chaos.

episodes.title: Bart vs. Itchy & Scratchy
episodes.plot: Bart's friends start a boys rights activist group to protest Krusty's all-female reboot of Itchy and Scratchy. When they catch Bart enjoying it, they kick him out, so he joins Bossy Riot, a militant feminist gang of sixth-grade girls.

episodes.title: Girl's in the Band
episodes.plot: Homer works extra shifts at the plant so Lisa can play in the Capitol City Youth Philharmonic.

episodes.title: I'm Just a Girl Who Can't Say D'oh
episodes.plot: Marge becomes Director of Springfield's local theater, armed with Lisa's script resembling "Hamilton"; Homer joins a baby class with Maggie, and takes a liking to supervisor Chloe.

episodes.title: D'oh Canada
episodes.plot: Lisa is mistakenly given political asylum in Canada during a family trip to Niagara Falls.

episodes.title: Woo-Hoo Dunnit?
episodes.plot: The documentary crime series "Dateline: Springfield" goes in-depth to solve the case of Lisa's missing college fund.

episodes.title: Crystal Blue-Haired Persuasion
episodes.plot: Marge starts a business selling healing crystals and other New Age products to the naive mothers of Springfield when Homer's job cuts children's health-care benefits, leading Marge to use the crystals as a cheaper solution for Bart's ADD.
